msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 3: Simultaneously, however, the eternal spiritual presence, the I AM, is always moving deep within the psyche, knocking at the door of awareness to be acknowledged as what we are at the most fundamental ...
#: paragraph:3,sentence:13
msgid "Thus, “divine discontent” or “spiritual deprivation,” to use Mother Teresa’s phrase, becomes more pronounced as our worldly goals and our budding spiritual inclinations begin to clash."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 3: Simultaneously, however, the eternal spiritual presence, the I AM, is always moving deep within the psyche, knocking at the door of awareness to be acknowledged as what we are at the most fundamental ...
#: paragraph:3,sentence:14
msgid "Consolidating our lives under the guidance of one thought system rather than two and adopting a single purpose of forgiveness allow the discomfort and uncertainty to diminish and finally disappear."
msgstr ""

