#: paragraph:4,sentence:16
msgid "Like most people, Bill presumed he was organizing his life according to his personal priorities, but as I assembled the details of his life, it became clear he was being led inexorably, step by step, to his own awakening."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 4: Like most people, Bill presumed he was organizing his life according to his personal priorities, but as I assembled the details of his life, it became clear he was being led inexorably, step by step, ...
#: paragraph:4,sentence:17
msgid "His personal story, with its trials and triumphs, waxes, wanes, and finally closes, but not before he demonstrates how to lay aside the quest for the “best of both worlds”—that unsatisfactory mix of love and fear—to pursue the single goal of peace of mind."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 4: Like most people, Bill presumed he was organizing his life according to his personal priorities, but as I assembled the details of his life, it became clear he was being led inexorably, step by step, ...
#: paragraph:4,sentence:18
msgid "He also makes it clear that you can be “in the world but not of it” and accomplish the only feat that really matters—waking up."
msgstr ""

