#: paragraph:6,sentence:27
msgid "He used to laugh about his response to situations where he thought he had been unduly elevated, saying, “When they started that, I’d just have to smoke cigarettes and say ‘shit’!” Now, he would want people to know his shortcomings and not evade issues he found challenging."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 6: Of all forms of recognition, Bill most objected to being sanctified or put on a pedestal. In the early days, some ACIM teachers were inclined to do just that. He used to laugh about his response to si...
#: paragraph:6,sentence:28
msgid "Although he insisted on seeing himself as ordinary, most of his friends did not."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 6: Of all forms of recognition, Bill most objected to being sanctified or put on a pedestal. In the early days, some ACIM teachers were inclined to do just that. He used to laugh about his response to si...
#: paragraph:6,sentence:29
msgid "Therefore, to honor what would certainly be Bill’s request, I present him here as a beloved equal, a dear friend, and unwitting mentor to so many."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 6: Of all forms of recognition, Bill most objected to being sanctified or put on a pedestal. In the early days, some ACIM teachers were inclined to do just that. He used to laugh about his response to si...
#: paragraph:6,sentence:30
msgid "One wonders if he ever totally realized how greatly he touched others."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 6: Of all forms of recognition, Bill most objected to being sanctified or put on a pedestal. In the early days, some ACIM teachers were inclined to do just that. He used to laugh about his response to si...
#: paragraph:6,sentence:31
msgid "In discussing this gift with him, in true egalitarian fashion he would ask us to apply that same question to our own lives."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 6: Of all forms of recognition, Bill most objected to being sanctified or put on a pedestal. In the early days, some ACIM teachers were inclined to do just that. He used to laugh about his response to si...
#: paragraph:6,sentence:32
msgid "And so we should."
msgstr ""

