#: paragraph:9,sentence:41
msgid "During his ten years in California, the last chapter of his life, Bill often told the stories of his youth, his career path, and the circumstances surrounding the scribing of the Course, almost always with a humorous twist."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 9: During his ten years in California, the last chapter of his life, Bill often told the stories of his youth, his career path, and the circumstances surrounding the scribing of the Course, almost always...
#: paragraph:9,sentence:42
msgid "He used to say he would probably tell those stories until he was finally comfortable with them, as if telling and retelling them was a sort of soul-liberating confession."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 9: During his ten years in California, the last chapter of his life, Bill often told the stories of his youth, his career path, and the circumstances surrounding the scribing of the Course, almost always...
#: paragraph:9,sentence:43
msgid "In particular, he often commented that if we thought studying and practicing the Course was difficult, we should have experienced the complications of scribing it."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 9: During his ten years in California, the last chapter of his life, Bill often told the stories of his youth, his career path, and the circumstances surrounding the scribing of the Course, almost always...
#: paragraph:9,sentence:44
msgid "Therefore, we will read his tales from our current vantage point, which allows a more fleshed-out picture of him."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 9: During his ten years in California, the last chapter of his life, Bill often told the stories of his youth, his career path, and the circumstances surrounding the scribing of the Course, almost always...
#: paragraph:9,sentence:45
msgid "I have also included firsthand accounts of his impact on those who knew him, the healings that occurred for so many, as well as my own experience of a precious friendship with him."
msgstr ""

